  <summary date="2019-11-08T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Honest Campaigns Act of 2019

This bill directs the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) to revise its sponsorship identification rules. Specifically, the FCC must&#160;require&#160;a disclosure announcement for broadcast or origination cablecasting matter that is political or that involves the discussion of a controversial issue of public importance to include the names of significant donors to the person whose identity is required to be disclosed in such an announcement.</summary>
